                <fr:title text="Well-ordering principle">Well-ordering principle</fr:title>
                <fr:meta name="source">Dummit and Foote <fr:link href="/dummit-2004-abstract/" title="Abstract Algebra" uri="http://localhost:8000/dummit-2004-abstract/" display-uri="dummit-2004-abstract" type="local">Abstract Algebra</fr:link> Section 0.2</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Every nonempty subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\subseteq \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> has a minimal element:</html:p>
                <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\forall  A\subseteq \mathbb {N}\ldotp  A\neq \emptyset \implies  \exists  a\in  A\ldotp \forall  x\in  A\ldotp  a\leq  x.]]></fr:tex>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>12</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>http://localhost:8000/nt-0002/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>nt-0002</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/nt-0002/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Division algorithm">Division algorithm</fr:title>
                <fr:meta name="source">Dummit and Foote <fr:link href="/dummit-2004-abstract/" title="Abstract Algebra" uri="http://localhost:8000/dummit-2004-abstract/" display-uri="dummit-2004-abstract" type="local">Abstract Algebra</fr:link> Section 0.2</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>For any integers <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a,b\in \mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex>, there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q,r\in \mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0\leq  r<|b|]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a=qb+r]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
                <html:p>We could take <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A=\{a-qb\mid  q\in \mathbb {Z},a-qb\geq 0\}]]></fr:tex>, then apply the <fr:link href="/nt-0001/" title="Well-ordering principle" uri="http://localhost:8000/nt-0001/" display-uri="nt-0001" type="local">Well-ordering principle</fr:link> to give us <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex> as a minimal element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
