                <fr:route>/nt-0003/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Greatest common divisor">Greatest common divisor</fr:title>
                <fr:meta name="source">Dummit and Foote <fr:link href="/dummit-2004-abstract/" title="Abstract Algebra" uri="http://localhost:8000/dummit-2004-abstract/" display-uri="dummit-2004-abstract" type="local">Abstract Algebra</fr:link> Section 0.2</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a,b\in \mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex> are nonzero integers, there exists a unique positive integer called the <html:dfn>Greatest Common Divisor</html:dfn> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex>, usually denoted <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\gcd (a,b)]]></fr:tex>, such that:</html:p>
                <html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\gcd (a,b)\mathrel {\bigm |} a]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\gcd (a,b)\mathrel {\bigm |} b]]></fr:tex> (so <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\gcd (a,b)]]></fr:tex> is a common divisor of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex>)</html:li>
<html:li>if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e\mathrel {\bigm |} a]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e\mathrel {\bigm |} b]]></fr:tex> is another integer, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e\mathrel {\bigm |}\gcd (a,b)]]></fr:tex> (so <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\gcd (a,b)]]></fr:tex> is the <html:em>greatest</html:em> such divisor).</html:li></html:ol>
                <html:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\gcd (a,b)=1]]></fr:tex> we say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> and {b} are <html:dfn>Coprime</html:dfn> (or are <html:dfn>Relatively Prime</html:dfn>).</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
