                <fr:title text="Euler totient is multiplicative on products of coprime numbers">Euler totient is multiplicative on products of coprime numbers</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>exercise</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m,n\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> be coprime <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\gcd (m,n)=1]]></fr:tex>. Prove or find a counter-example: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi (mn)=\varphi (m)\varphi (n)]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
