                <fr:title text="Quotient set">Quotient set</fr:title>
                <fr:meta name="source">Dummit and Foote <fr:link href="/dummit-2004-abstract/" title="Abstract Algebra" uri="http://localhost:8000/dummit-2004-abstract/" display-uri="dummit-2004-abstract" type="local">Abstract Algebra</fr:link> Section 0.3</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link href="/nst-0011/" title="Equivalence relation" uri="http://localhost:8000/nst-0011/" display-uri="nst-0011" type="local">Equivalence relation</fr:link> on a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>. Then we define the <html:dfn>Quotient set</html:dfn>
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[X/R := \{[a]\mid  a\in  X\}]]></fr:tex>
is the set of <fr:link href="/nst-0012/" title="Equivalence class" uri="http://localhost:8000/nst-0012/" display-uri="nst-0012" type="local">equivalence classes</fr:link>. We have a natural surjective map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X\to  X/R]]></fr:tex> sending <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mapsto [a]]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
